<paragraph id="F1053680FFCBF547FF715E736112F92A" blockId="20.[151,1437,1557,1799]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
Type data: This species was described based on an undetermined number of male specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion id="337EF862FFCBF547FAF65E73652BF9BE" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Pernambuco state</collectingRegion>
, northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="89AD7610FFCBF547FE515E1765CDF9BE" box="[439,511,1629,1655]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. A 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFCBF547FDC55E176648F9BE" box="[547,634,1629,1655]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">syntype</typeStatus>
was found at 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFCBF547FCFF5E1767B1F9BE" box="[793,899,1629,1655]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
being here designated the 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFCBF547FB575E176129F9BE" box="[1201,1307,1629,1655]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: Type H. 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFCBF547FD485ECB66F3F952" box="[686,705,1665,1691]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">T</collectionCode>
. [red-rimmed circular label, printed]\ B.M. 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFCBF547FB475ECB60D5F952" box="[1185,1255,1665,1691]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">TYPE</collectionCode>
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFCBF547FB0A5ECB6103F952" box="[1260,1329,1665,1691]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">HYM</collectionCode>
. [printed] 17b 1171 [handwritten]\ [circular label] Braz [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="36BA4D03FFCBF547FC615EEF60ACF976" authority="Smith" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[903,1182,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perforator">
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFCBF547FC615EEF6067F976" box="[903,1109,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Centris perforator</emphasis>
Smith
</taxonomicName>
(Type). [handwritten]. The 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFCBF547FEF35E83654EF92A" box="[277,380,1737,1763]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">lectotype</typeStatus>
is in good condition and is coded 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFCBF547FD1A5E826754F92A" box="[764,870,1736,1763]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
010812625 in the 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFCBF547FBD75E8360A9F92A" box="[1073,1179,1737,1763]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
data portal.
</paragraph>
